High School Football
September 4, 2020 - 7 PM
Commerce Vs Galena KS

- Social distancing required for all spectators.
- Face coverings are highly encouraged.
- For Health and Safety, only players, school personnel and officials are allowed on the field.
- To help with social and physical distancing, we will be opening the track area on the curves(both ends-10 yard line to 10 yard line) for spectators to sit in lawn chairs(please stay off the grass area).
-Students PreK-8 must be accompanied and stay with a parent/guardian to be admitted for the event.

Printed rosters will not be available. The rosters for tonight's game can be viewed here - https://5il.co/km91

Varsity Football Admission
Adults- $5
Students- $3

post_text:
https://forms.gle/jjfbbp9dtewrxoUS7

Virtual school enrollment is winding down. If you haven't already enrolled and would like to enroll in Commerce Virtual School, please do so by August 3rd, 2020. We need accurate numbers to assist in our planning.

If you're a Commerce resident and have transferred to another online virtual school in the past, please consider returning to Commerce Schools now that we have this option available.

These are just a few of the benefits we offer over the statewide virtual schools -
1. Local teachers that are available to assist you.
2. Ability to participate in Commerce athletics, band and other extracurricular activities.
3. Tax dollars staying at home and not being shipped to for profit companies.

We have already welcomed back several former Epic students, join them and reap the benefits of local education.

post_text:
The Oklahoma State Dept. of Ed. has made strong recommendations to schools concerning county COVID-19 levels.

Commerce Public Schools will be following these recommendations, as put out by OSDE. You can find protocols here - https://sde.ok.gov/sites/default/files/documents/files/Oklahoma%20Schools%20Safety%20Protocols%20Draft.pdf

Ottawa county is currently at "Orange Level 1" as far as the alert system is concerned. This is calculated weekly on each Friday.

You can find the weekly levels here - https://coronavirus.health.ok.gov/covid-19-alert-system

These numbers will be used weekly to determine what level Commerce will be using in our Return To Learn plan. Levels and CPS response will be communicated to parents through our website, Facebook, Twitter, all call and text.

post_text:
Parents - All returning students have to be re-enrolled in Commerce Schools yearly. This year we've moved all enrollment forms inside of your powerschool login for your ease. Please log in to your parent account and select forms on the left. There are 9 online forms to complete for returning students. It should take you less then 10 minutes to complete the forms. Please complete the enrollment forms for all of your students in your parent login. If you login and the screen looks like the picture attached you need to complete the forms for that student.

Blue Leaves = You need to complete this form
Green or Yellow Leaves = You have completed that form.

If you do not have your parent login simply email enrollment@commercetigers.net and we'll provide you with your login credentials.

Our powerschool web address is https://ps.commercetigers.net/public/home.html

If your student is or was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma’s Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your 2020 estimated income. The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020 deadline at https://secure.okcollegestart.org/applications/Oklahoma_Promise/apply.html?application_id=3544. You will be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal tax return when completed to verify that your 2020 income was under $55,000. The application will be held as pending until the tax documentation is received. Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu.

post_text:
Commerce High School is proud to join the nationwide campaign on Friday to honor the 2020 Senior Class!

High schools around Oklahoma and across the country are banding together to honor the 2020 senior class amidst the coronavirus pandemic.

On Friday, April 10, at 8:20 p.m., all Commerce High School Athletic Field lights and other outdoor stadiums around the state and country will turn on their lights for 20 minutes to show their appreciation for the senior class, families, coaches and athletes as part of the “Be the Light” campaign.

The lights are a beacon to show the Senior Class we are thinking of them and to remind them there will be a time where we will be all together once again.

The “Be the Light” campaign has been spreading across the nation as schools look for a way to celebrate their graduating seniors who are having their final memories in high school stripped away due to the outbreak.

Go Tigers!

post_text:
City of Commerce News Release

The safety and security of our schools cannot be understated. All threats to our schools and students are taken very seriously and are investigated thoroughly.

On November 19, 2019, a report was received from Commerce Public Schools that a high school student allegedly threatened to bring a gun to school. An investigation immediately started concerning the allegations.

The investigation has consisted of interviewing more than 15 students including the student that allegedly made the statement and also reviewing hours of video surveillance of the school. The student that was accused of making a threat has been cooperating with law enforcement and allowed a search of his residence where no firearms were found.

The investigation has concluded and the allegations that a threat was made has been determined to be unfounded.

To make students and parents more comfortable, extra security will be at the school throughout the week.

Chief Ray Horn
Commerce Police Department
